{"title_page": "Tom Acker", "text_new": "{{no footnotes|date=March 2013}}\n\n{{Infobox baseball biography\n|name=Tom Acker\n|position=Pitcher\n|image=Tom Acker.jpg\n|bats=Right\n|throws=Right\n|birth_date={{Birth date and age|1930|3|7}}\n|birth_place=[[Paterson, New Jersey]]\n|debutleague = MLB\n|debutdate= April 20 \n|debutyear= 1956\n|debutteam= Cincinnati Redlegs\n|finalleague = MLB\n|finaldate=September 20\n|finalyear=1959\n|finalteam=Cincinnati Redlegs\n|statleague = MLB\n|stat1label=[[Win\u2013loss record (pitching)|Win\u2013loss record]]\n|stat1value=19\u201313\n|stat2label=[[Earned run average]]\n|stat2value=4.12\n|stat3label=[[Strikeouts]]\n|stat3value=256\n|teams=\n* [[Cincinnati Redlegs]] / [[Cincinnati Reds|Reds]] ({{Baseball year|1956}}\u2013{{Baseball year|1959}})\n}}\n'''Thomas James Acker''' (born March 7, 1930) is a former [[Major League Baseball]] [[pitcher]]. \n\n==Biography==\nA right-hander, Acker was signed by the [[New York Giants (NL)|New York Giants]] before the 1948 season.  \n\nOn October 14, 1951, he was traded by the Triple-A Buffalo Bisons with pitcher [[Moe Savransky]] to the [[Cincinnati Redlegs]] for outfielder [[Jim Bolger (baseball)|Jim Bolger]]. He played with the Redlegs from 1956 to 1959.\n\nThe majority of Acker's 153 appearances were as a [[relief pitcher]], though he did start 23 games. During his career, he had 256 [[strikeouts]] in 380.1 total innings. His [[K/9IP]] was 6.06, which was higher than the [[National League]] average at that time. \n\nIn 1957 he finished in the [[National League]] top ten for [[games pitched]], [[winning percentage]], and [[hit batsmen]]. Acker handled 68 out of 69 [[total chances]] successfully for a [[fielding percentage]] of .986 during his four seasons.\n\n==External links==\n{{Baseballstats |mlb=110034 |espn= |br=a/ackerto01 |fangraphs=1000031 |brm=acker-001tho }}\n\n{{Portal bar|Baseball|Biography}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Acker, Tom}}\n[[Category:1930 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Cincinnati Redlegs players]]\n[[Category:Baseball players from New Jersey]]\n[[Category:Major League Baseball pitchers]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Paterson, New Jersey]]\n[[Category:Oshkosh Giants players]]\n[[Category:Tulsa Oilers (baseball) players]]\n[[Category:Knoxville Smokies players]]\n[[Category:Nashville Vols players]]\n[[Category:Buffalo Bisons (minor league) players]]\n[[Category:Richmond Virginians (minor league) players]]\n\n{{US-baseball-pitcher-1930s-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{no footnotes|date=March 2013}}\n\n{{Infobox baseball biography\n|name=Tom Acker\n|position=Pitcher\n|image=Tom Acker.jpg\n|bats=Right\n|throws=Right\n|birth_date={{Birth date and age|1930|3|7}}\n|birth_place=[[Paterson, New Jersey]]\n|debutleague = MLB\n|debutdate= April 20 \n|debutyear= 1956\n|debutteam= Cincinnati Redlegs\n|finalleague = MLB\n|finaldate=September 20\n|finalyear=1959\n|finalteam=Cincinnati Redlegs\n|statleague = MLB\n|stat1label=[[Win\u2013loss record (pitching)|Win\u2013loss record]]\n|stat1value=19\u201313\n|stat2label=[[Earned run average]]\n|stat2value=4.12\n|stat3label=[[Strikeouts]]\n|stat3value=256\n|teams=\n* [[Cincinnati Redlegs]] / [[Cincinnati Reds|Reds]] ({{Baseball year|1956}}\u2013{{Baseball year|1959}})\n}}\n'''Thomas James Acker''' (born March 7, 1930) is a former [[Major League Baseball]] [[pitcher]]. \n\n==Biography==\nA right-hander, Acker was signed by the [[New York Giants (NL)|New York Giants]] before the 1948 season.  On October 14, 1951, he was traded by Buffalo with pitcher [[Moe Savransky]] to the [[Cincinnati Redlegs]] for outfielder [[Jim Bolger (baseball)|Jim Bolger]].<ref name=autogenerated2>[https://www.baseball-reference.com/players/s/savramo01.shtml Moe Savransky Stats | Baseball-Reference.com<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> He played for the Redlegs from 1956 to 1959.\n\nThe majority of Acker's 153 appearances were as a [[relief pitcher]], but he did start 23 games. During his career, he had 256 [[strikeouts]] in 380.3 total innings. His [[K/9IP]] was 6.06, which was higher than the [[National League]] average at that time. In 1957 he finished in the [[National League]] top ten for [[games pitched]], [[winning percentage]], and [[hit batsmen]]. Acker handled 68 out of 69 [[total chances]] successfully for a [[fielding percentage]] of .986 during his four seasons.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Baseballstats |mlb=110034 |espn= |br=a/ackerto01 |fangraphs=1000031 |brm=acker-001tho }}\n\n{{Portal bar|Baseball|Biography}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Acker, Tom}}\n[[Category:1930 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Cincinnati Redlegs players]]\n[[Category:Baseball players from New Jersey]]\n[[Category:Major League Baseball pitchers]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Paterson, New Jersey]]\n[[Category:Oshkosh Giants players]]\n[[Category:Tulsa Oilers (baseball) players]]\n[[Category:Knoxville Smokies players]]\n[[Category:Nashville Vols players]]\n[[Category:Buffalo Bisons (minor league) players]]\n[[Category:Richmond Virginians (minor league) players]]\n\n{{US-baseball-pitcher-1930s-stub}}\n", "name_user": "69.158.87.97", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(\u2192\u200eBiography)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tom_Acker"}
